ale":"1035–Deceased","1075–Female":"1075–Deceased","1060–Male":"1060–Deceased","–Male":"Deceased","1035":"1035","abt 1030":"about 1030","1075":"1075","1030":"1030","1060":"1060","about 1055":"about 1055","Morpeth, Northumberland, England":"Morpeth, Northumberland, England","Normandy, FRANCE":"Normandy, France","of Normandy, France":"Normandy, France","England":"England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Merley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French: derivative of <i>merle</i> ‘blackbird’ (see   Merle  ). Compare   Marlette  .","History: Gédéon Merlet/Marlet from Roussy-le-Village in Moselle, France, married Margriet Martijn in Leiden, the Netherlands, in 1644, died in Piscataway, NJ, <i>c.</i> 1682. In 1662 they emigrated to the Dutch colony of New Amsterdam in New Netherland (now New York City, NY). Gédéon's name is listed (as Gidéon Merlet) in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors."],"variants":[{"name":"Marlette","meanings":["Americanized form of French <b>Marlet</b> or of its variant   Merlet  . Altered ending reflects the Canadian and American French practice of sounding the final <i>-t</i>. Compare   Malott  ,   Malotte  ,   Marlatt  ,   Marlett  ,   Mellott  , and   Melott  .","History: Gédéon Merlet/Marlet from Roussy-le-Village in Moselle, France, married Margriet Martijn in Leiden, the Netherlands, in 1644, died in Piscataway, NJ, <i>c.</i> 1682. In 1662 they emigrated to the Dutch colony of New Amsterdam in New Netherland (now New York City, NY). Gédéon's name is listed (as Gidéon Merlet) in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors."]},{"name":"Merle","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Pierre, Etienne, Henri, Jean-Paul.","French, English (of Norman origin), German, and Dutch: nickname, possibly for a good or habitual singer or whistler, from Old French, Middle High German <i>merle</i> ‘blackbird’ (from Latin <i>merula</i>). See also Italian and Spanish   Merlo  .","French: habitational name from (Le) Merle, the name of several places in various parts of France."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert de Merley was born about 1030, in Normandy, France as the son of Merlay. He married Emma Bastenbough about 1055, in England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"abt 1030–":"umbes 1030–Surnud","1030–Male":"1030–Surnud","1035–Female":"1035–Surnud","1075–Female":"1075–Surnud","1060–Male":"1060–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1035":"1035","abt 1030":"umbes 1030","1075":"1075","1030":"1030","1060":"1060","about 1055":"umbes 1055","Morpeth, Northumberland, England":"Morpeth, Northumberland, England","Normandy, FRANCE":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa","of Normandy, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa","England":"England"},"fi":{"abt 1030–":"noin 1030–Kuollut","1030–Male":"1030–Kuollut","1035–Female":"1035–Kuollut","1075–Female":"1075–Kuollut","1060–Male":"1060–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1035":"1035","abt 1030":"noin 1030","1075":"1075","1030":"1030","1060":"1060","about 1055":"noin 1055","Morpeth, Northumberland, England":"Morpeth, Northumberland, England","Normandy, FRANCE":"Normandie, Ranska","of Normandy, France":"Normandie, Ranska","England":"England"},"fr":{"abt 1030–":"environ 1030–Décédé","1030–Male":"1030–Décédé","1035–Female":"1035–Décédée","1075–Female":"1075–Décédée","1060–Male":"1060–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","1035":"1035","abt 1030":"environ 1030","1075":"1075","1030":"1030","1060":"1060","about 1055":"environ 1055","Morpeth, Northumberland, England":"Morpeth, Northumberland, Angleterre","Normandy, FRANCE":"Normandie, France","of Normandy, France":"Normandie, France","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Robert de Merley est né environ 1030, à Normandie, France, fils de Merlay. Il a épousé Emma Bastenbough environ 1055, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 2 fils."},"de":{"abt 1030–":"um 1030–Verstorben","1030–Male":"1030–Verstorben","1035–Female":"1035–Verstorben","1075–Female":"1075–Verstorben","1060–Male":"1060–Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1035":"1035","abt 1030":"um 1030","1075":"1075","1030":"1030","1060":"1060","about 1055":"um 1055","Morpeth, Northumberland, England":"Morpeth, Northumberland, England","Normandy, FRANCE":"Normandie, Frankreich","of Normandy, Fr